Later, as he visited Prime Minister Dr Joseph Muscat at the Auberge de Castille he added: ‘I’m sorry you’ve got me instead of Catherine.’

Royal sources say the Duchess, who was due to deliver a message from the Queen to the people of Malta, was ‘absolutely desperate’ to make the trip but her medics advised against her travelling.

She is believed to be resting at home at Kensington Palace with Prince George and his nanny.

The Duke also joked it would be some time before he would bring the couple’s rumbustious 14-month-old son to the country.

